main event: A very bright object covered with lights was observed proceeding northeast from a home in Elizabeth, NJ at 0143 hours on August 14, 1952.
interesting points: The object was detected through ground-radar as a probable aircraft,The sighting lasted for 3-5 minutes,Radio contact was secured 3/4 mile away,The incident was reported by Captain Maguire of the Elizabeth Police Department,The observer was a 16-year-old resident of Elizabeth, NJ.
sighted object: a very bright object covered with lights
